      • compare

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> compare(java.lang.Object obj)
                                         throws PropertyInconsistentException
        Compare two ComponentType and return a ComponentType containing the differences between the two. The objects being compared may be a derived class of ComponentType. That is acceptable. The diff is done only for the ComponentType members. Currently this does not compare the 'optional' AttributesType.
        Returns:
        Returns a List of two Objects. The first Object is a boolean: false=match, true=mismatch The second Object is a ComponentType with match/mismatch
        Throws:
        PropertyInconsistentException
